chunk_content: Specimen collection for recency testing at the time of initial diagnosis is recommended, but other service delivery points may be considered if the test for recent infection is conducted within a short period of initial HIV diagnosis. Ideally, the test for recent infection, or specimen collection if testing is performed at an alternate point (e.g., facility or hub laboratory), should be conducted at the same time as diagnosis. If guidelines specify that viral load testing be 94 conducted alongside the test for recent infection as part of a RITA, then these results should be recorded in addition to the RTRI results. T Because RITA results will take longer than RTRI, do not wait for RITA results to report the RTRI results. E S RITA results should be reported only during the same MER reporting period when the RTRI was T conducted. This only applies to MER reporting; all RITA results should always be reported to national I N systems.
